Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util

package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util
The util package contains several classes aimed at helping RapidSmith users do a variety of operations such as install RapidSmith, convert files, and run certain Xilinx tools from within RapidSmith.
  • Class
    Description
    ArgsParser
    This class parses command-line arguments in a mostly-Posix compliant form.
    BrowseDevice
    This class is a simple method to browse device information by tile.
    DesignCompare
    This class compares two designs to check if they are identical.
    DesignDiff
     
    FamilyType
    These names are taken from the Xilinx tool 'partgen.' They are the architecture names given, however, here they are called the family name.
    FileConverter
     
    FileTools
    This class is specifically written to allow for efficient file import/export of different semi-primitive data types and structures.
    FlattenDesign
     
    HardMacroGenerator
    This class reads an XDL design file and converts it to a hard macro.
    Installer
    This class will create the device and wire enumerator files necessary for RapidSmith to operate.
    MergeStaticNets
    This class will read in an XDL design and unroute and merge all static source (GND/VCC) nets into GLOBAL_LOGIC0 and GLOBAL_LOGIC1 and also remove all sources (TIEOFFs/SLICEs).
    MessageGenerator
     
    PartNameTools
    This class is to aid manipulating and converting Xilinx part names and the FamilyType enum.
    PatchGenerator
    This class generates a patch java class used for mapping missing internal pin names to external pin names for primitive sites missing the mappings from the XDLRC report file.
    RunXilinxTools
    This is a generic class which has several static methods to call Xilinx tools from within the RapidSmith framework.
    StreamGobbler
     
    StringPool
     
    TileAndPrimitiveEnumerator
    This class generates java files for the device package for Xilinx FPGAs to create enumerations for tile type names and primitive type names.
    UnrouteNets
     
    XDLDesignChecker
    This class is meant to debug problem with XDL files.
